romises of political control. These works, created in opposition and proximity to the extraction of cultural, political, and territorial resources, demonstrate how Indigenous claims to life and land matter to rethinking and unmaking the social and ecological devastations of the colonial world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAmerican literaturexIndian authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aOjibwa IndiansxColonizationzMinnesota. 0aOjibwa IndianszMinnesotazMinneapolis Metropolitan Area. 0aOjibwa IndianszMinnesotazSaint Paul Metropolitan Area. 0aOjibwa artzMinnesota. 0aOjibwa literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aSettler colonialism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh1 aLines, Horizon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059363?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059363423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059363/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles